parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Defective Seat Belt and Door Latch Switch
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt and door latch switch can cause the seat belt to malfunction, leading to a lack of restraint for the passenger or driver, which can increase the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt cannot be utilized
the passenger's seat belt intermittently fails to engage when closing the door
the seat belt does not work at all
the motorized shoulder belt remains in the forward position
the cable is compressed and forced out of its track
the belt fails to retract
the belt locks up and will not release.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the motorized shoulder belt can cause the belt to remain in the forward position, leading to a lack of restraint for the passenger or driver, which can increase the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The motorized shoulder belt remains in the forward position
the cable is compressed and forced out of its track
the belt fails to retract.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the belt retractors can cause the seat belt to malfunction, leading to a lack of restraint for the passenger or driver, which can increase the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The belt retractors fail
the belt does not retract
the belt locks up and will not release.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Warped brake rotors can cause poor braking performance, leading to increased stopping distances and potentially accidents.

noise or stress sounds when braking
warped rotors.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the door latch can cause the shoulder belt anchorage to remain at the A-pillar when the door is closed, leading to the failure of the automatic seat belts to engage when the vehicle is started, which can increase the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt does not slide on the rail properly
the automatic seat belts do not engage when the vehicle is started
the shoulder belt anchorage remains at the A-pillar when the door is closed.
